Riſe up thou) or riſe up for thy ſelfe, and for thy good;
〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
Surge tibi. ſit not ſtill under darkneſſe and ſuperſtition, lye no longer under the burthen of legall rites and ceremonies, for the time is comming on that thou ſhalt not be under rudiments and traditions, but under a more pure Goſpel diſpenſation. Thus the Apoſtle bids us ariſe from ſin, he ſaith, Awake thou that ſleepeſt, and ariſe from the dead, and Chriſt ſhall give thee light, Epheſ. 5. 13. That is, let us ſit no longer in ſin, but ariſe, that Chriſt may give us light.
